channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Kamala Harris Is Fast-Tracking Citizenship Applications in an Attempt to 'Reshape the Electorate'
Arizona law requiring proof of citizenship to vote supported by 24 state AGs in emergency stay with SCOTUS
item.description: An emergency application filed in support of HB 2492 in Arizona would require everyone to show proof of citizenship to vote, even with mail-in ballots.

item.title: Kamala Harris Set to Unveil Economic Plan
item.description: In the first major policy address of her campaign, Vice President Kamala Harris is expected on Friday to unveil an economic plan that tackles the high cost of housing and groceries, two sectors hit hard by inflation.

item.title: Twelve New Felony Charges Filed Against Operator of Illegal CCP-Linked Biolab
Critics blast Harris' grasp of inflation, attack on business ahead of policy speech: 'Lunatic behavior'
item.description: Vice President Harris will unveil her economic plan Friday, striking out against corporate "price gouging," a tack conservative detractors say ignores the real causes of inflation.

item.title: Jim McLaughlin to Newsmax: Biased Polling Gives Biased Results
item.description: Pollster Jim McLaughlin told Newsmax that polls, especially biased ones, don't always tell the full story.

item.title: Biden/Harris Maryland Event Has Embarrassing Moment When Dozens of People Walk Out
Minnesota business owners sound alarm on Harris' 'nightmare' VP pick : 'Really bad for the US'
item.description: Small business owners in Minnesota said that it has been a "nightmare" working under Gov. Tim Walz's leadership.

item.title: John Bolton to Newsmax: Afghanistan Withdrawal 'Catastrophic'
item.description: Former Ambassador to the United Nations John Bolton told Newsmax on Thursday that the Trump administration worked out the details of a deal to withdraw from Afghanistan that the Biden administration "implemented poorly."

item.title: Illegal Alien Peruvian Gang Leader Suspected in 23 Murders Arrested in Upstate New York
'Rent is too damn high': Rosen panned for Biden-aligned votes, high housing costs
item.description: Rosen is being targeted for high housing costs and continued inflation after voting in favor of President Biden's spending bill that sought to ease economic struggles during COVID-19.

item.title: Trump: Harris Betrayed Israel to Pacify Dems' Hamas Caucus
item.description: Former President Donald Trump said Thursday that Vice President Kamala Harris has betrayed Israel "to appease the Hamas caucus and the radical Democrat Party" and that if he's elected in November, he will stand with Israel and protect America's Jewish community.

item.title: REPORT: Ukraine Blew Up Nord Stream Pipeline, Zelenskyy Tried to Stop It but Failed
Trump conducts no-holds-barred press conference while Harris continues dodging media
item.description: Former President Trump held yet another hours-long press conference Thursday—his second this month—in an effort to draw a stark contrast between his candidacy and his opponent.

item.title: Sen. Schmitt to Newsmax: Harris Is 'Embodiment of the Left'
item.description: Sen. Eric Schmitt, R-Mo., told Newsmax on Thursday that while President Joe Biden has been a "puppet for the left," Democrat presidential nominee Kamala Harris is "the embodiment of the left."Harris is a "true believer," Schmitt said on "Prime News."
